message.content:
1. The right rectus femoris and right vastus intermedius CSD decreased in both groups.
2. In the EMS group, the right rectus femoris and right vastus intermedius CSD decreased from 1.42 ± 0.48 to 1.31 ± 0.45 cm.
3. The decrease in the EMS group was statistically significant with a P value of 0.001.
4. In the control group, the right rectus femoris and right vastus intermedius CSD decreased from 1.59 ± 0.53 to 1.37 ± 0.5 cm.
5. The decrease in the control group was statistically significant with a P value of 0.002.
6. In the EMS group, the right rectus femoris and right vastus intermedius CSD decreased from 0.91 ± 0.39 to 0.81 ± 0.38 cm.
7. The decrease in the EMS group was statistically significant with a P value of 0.001.
8. In the control group, the right rectus femoris and right vastus intermedius CSD decreased from 1.40 ± 0.64 to 1.11 ± 0.56 cm.
9. The decrease in the control group was statistically significant with a P value of 0.004.
